<br>
Your Main Role<br>
That is to heal.  Presently we have been using a triage&lt;sp?&gt; method for this.  After we have cleared to the dragon the druids and clerics will be assembled in a reasonably safe area to heal up those that need it as they come back.  Anything that would improve your total mana before this time would be helpful.<br>
<br>
Resist Gear<br>
Magic resist and the appropriate fire or cold resist is needed to be effective.  Minimums for this are generally 75 for each and better.  This is needed regardless of role and what buffs will give you after wards.  Even though you will be out of direct harm's way for most of this, dragon breath weapons do more damage than their actual attacks, which are claws for over 200 and kicks for over 100.  <br>
<br>
Hot Key Setup<br>
It is now possible to attach a message when casting a spell, use it.  This will both reassure the person you are healing and reduce the chance that others may unnecessarily heal your healed target.  <br>
<br>
Mana Management<br>
Your heals are not as good as a cleric's, pure casters have no hitpoints.  Make sure the clerics let you know where they are for mana and vice versa.  Use all of the healers mana as whole as best can.  Remember that trying to keep a pure caster alive that has earned the attention of a dragon is throwing good mana after bad. A dragon can push their hp's to zero faster than they can be replaced.  They are bound close, get all their mana back upon return with their health as well.  A dead tank is a gone tank.  No tanks = failed raid.  <br>
<br>
Triage Group<br>
Perhaps someone that is a healer here could post what they do to work together.  Avoiding situations that a person is over healed is important, making sure that someone steps forward to take up healing duties is important lest someone find themself standing in front of a group of healers waiting while the healers expect someone else to cast first.  What do you do to manage dragon aggro, it would be foolish for one cleric to cast CH til OOM and then find themselves summoned to the dragon when they sit to med.   What do you guys do?<br>
